frus:attachment.p:
—In authorizing representation allowances, it specifically provides for
                        reimbursement of representational expenses incurred by family members (Sec.
                        461, p. 31);

—It provides for training and orientation grants to facilitate functional
                        training for family members, whereas the present law authorizes such grants
                        only for orientation and language training (Sec. 704, p. 52);
